parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Head gasket failure can cause engine overheating, loss of coolant, and engine damage, leading to costly repairs and potential safety risks.
A faulty MAF sensor can cause poor engine performance, decreased fuel efficiency, and increased emissions, leading to decreased vehicle safety and performance.
Harmonic balancer failure can cause engine vibration, noise, and damage to other engine components, leading to decreased vehicle safety and performance.
symptoms: Loud noise from the engine compartment

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission problems can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and strandings, leading to safety risks and inconvenience.
symptoms: vehicle jumps in and out of gear

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine stalling can cause accidents, strandings, and safety risks, especially when occurring at high speeds or in heavy traffic.
Failure of engine components can cause engine damage, decreased performance, and safety risks.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the motorized seat belt retractor can cause the seat belt to become stuck, leading to entrapment, strangulation, or choking hazards, which can result in serious injury or death.
symptoms: The seat belt retractor performs poorly
the seat belt is tightly placed on the occupant
the shoulder belt is stuck on the track
the motorized seat belt shifts back and forth while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the lap belt buckle can cause the occupant to become trapped, leading to serious injury or death.
symptoms: The lap belt buckle would not release or unlock
the consumer had to cut the seat belt off.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the shoulder belt can cause the occupant to become unrestrained in the event of a crash, leading to serious injury or death.
symptoms: The shoulder belt failed to restrain the occupant in an accident
the shoulder belt is stuck on the track.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The accelerator pedal sticking can cause unexpected acceleration, loss of control, and increased risk of accidents.
